Fix: pin the CCM image back to 1.1.0

1. Find the CCM Deployment:
kubectl get deploy -n kube-system | grep cloud-controller-manager
kubectl get deploy cloud-controller-manager -n kube-system -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'

2. Patch the image tag to 1.1.0:
kubectl set image deployment/cloud-controller-manager \
  -n kube-system \
  cloud-controller-manager=<registry-path>/cloudstack-ccm:1.1.0

3. Watch it come back up healthy:
kubectl rollout status deployment/cloud-controller-manager -n kube-system
kubectl logs -n kube-system -l k8s-app=cloudstack-ccm -f
